Explanation:

I inspected controllers/invoices.js and the Invoice model (models/InvoiceModel.js) to determine the parameters used by the PATCH /invoices/{id} endpoint.

- The controller updateInvoice reads the invoice id from req.params (id) and the update payload from req.body (invoice). It also validates the id as a MongoDB ObjectId. Therefore the endpoint requires a path parameter "id" (string) and a request body containing the invoice object.
- The Invoice schema in models/InvoiceModel.js defines the invoice fields. I mapped the Mongoose schema types to Swagger 2.0 types:
  - Mongoose Date -> type: string, format: date-time
  - Mongoose String -> type: string
  - Mongoose Number -> type: number
  - Arrays and nested objects are represented with array/object schemas accordingly.
- I did not use $ref and did not add fields not present in the InvoiceModel.js file. The body parameter schema enumerates the fields from the model: dueDate, currency, items (with itemName/unitPrice/quantity/discount), rates, vat, total, subTotal, notes, status, invoiceNumber, type, creator, totalAmountReceived, client (name/email/phone/address), paymentRecords (amountPaid/datePaid/paymentMethod/note/paidBy), and createdAt.

